{"case_id": "cpython-tcl-windows-matrix-v2-001", "context_method": "llm-summary-v1-mock", "diagnoser": "real-agent-v1", "mode": "root_cause_diagnosis", "summary": "Two tests in test_tcl fail with AssertionError because the Tcl interface returns raw surrogate pairs ('\\ud83d\\udcbb') instead of the expected combined Unicode character ('\\U0001f4bb', the laptop emoji). Both test_eval_surrogates_in_result and test_evalfile_surrogates_in_result fail on this assertion, and the test is re-run but fails again, causing the job to exit with code 2.", "root_cause_category": "test_assertion", "root_cause": "The Tcl/tkinter interface on Windows does not recombine surrogate pairs into proper Unicode code points when returning results from tcl.eval(). The tests expect '<\\U0001f4bb>' but receive '<\\ud83d\\udcbb>' (the raw surrogate pair), indicating a regression in surrogate-pair handling in the _tkinter C extension or the Tcl library version (9.0.3) used.", "confidence": 0.95, "relevant_files": ["D:\\a\\cpython\\cpython\\Lib\\test\\test_tcl.py"], "relevant_tests": ["test.test_tcl.TclTest.test_eval_surrogates_in_result", "test.test_tcl.TclTest.test_evalfile_surrogates_in_result"], "evidence": [{"quote": "test_eval_surrogates_in_result (test.test_tcl.TclTest.test_eval_surrogates_in_result) ... FAIL", "reason": "Directly identifies the first failing test in the test_tcl module"}, {"quote": "test_evalfile_surrogates_in_result (test.test_tcl.TclTest.test_evalfile_surrogates_in_result) ... FAIL", "reason": "Directly identifies the second failing test in the test_tcl module"}, {"quote": "AssertionError: '<\\ud83d\\udcbb>' != '<ðŸ'»>'", "reason": "Shows the actual vs expected mismatch: surrogate pair returned instead of combined Unicode character"}, {"quote": "self.assertEqual(tcl.eval(r'set a \"<\\ud83d\\udcbb>\"'), '<\\U0001f4bb>')", "reason": "Shows the test expects the surrogate pair to be recombined into U+1F4BB but it is not"}, {"quote": "patchlevel = 9.0.3", "reason": "Identifies the Tcl version (9.0.3) in use, which may handle surrogate pairs differently"}, {"quote": "test test_tcl failed", "reason": "Confirms the test module failed both on first run and re-run"}, {"quote": "1 test failed again:\n    test_tcl", "reason": "Confirms the failure is reproducible (not a flake), as the re-run also failed"}, {"quote": "##[error]Process completed with exit code 2.", "reason": "Confirms the job exited with a non-zero exit code due to the test failure"}], "suggested_fix": "Investigate the surrogate pair recombination logic in the _tkinter C extension for compatibility with Tcl 9.0.3, which may have changed how it handles surrogate pairs in string results. The test at Lib/test/test_tcl.py line 57 and line 292 expects surrogate pairs to be merged into proper Unicode code points when returned from tcl.eval().", "input": {"context_path": "results/v2/stress/llm-summary-v1-mock/cpython-tcl-windows-matrix-v2-001.txt", "context_tokens_estimate": 1863}, "usage": {"processing_tokens_estimate": 0, "output_tokens_estimate": 1055}, "metadata": {"provider": "command", "prompt_sha256": "ecffdf03c99a91b0f8f75e086720d9fb8db96af0d9dae5285baf679c9c9d28de", "runtime_ms": 39626.347, "cache_key": "1043a28c5a938ab9a84b5353654f67348445fedbec86197329cd34db0ad56815", "provider_error": null, "provider_error_detail": null, "command": "python3 /Users/eyuansu62/llm_judge/cli-token-killer/cilog-bench/examples/diagnosis_shim_claude_agent.py", "model_info": {"provider_name": "anthropic", "requested_model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "resolved_model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "base_url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1", "usage": {"input_tokens": 36600, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1037, "service_tier": "standard", "inference_geo": "global"}}, "diagnoser_config_name": null, "diagnoser_config_sha256": "a87dd5e5ce51e6205be617b7a3c45c1647376786e44852f4b639352884f