{"case_id": "nodejs-test-debugger-exec-timeout-v2-001", "context_method": "llm-summary-v1-mock", "diagnoser": "real-agent-v1", "mode": "root_cause_diagnosis", "summary": "The test `parallel/test-debugger-exec` failed because it timed out (15000ms) while waiting for the debugger to emit an initial break message matching `/break (?:on start )?in/i`. The debugger attached successfully but never sent the expected break-on-start notification, causing the test to throw a Timeout error.", "root_cause_category": "test_assertion", "root_cause": "test/parallel/test-debugger-exec.js timed out after 15000ms waiting for the pattern /break (?:on start )?in/i from the Node.js debugger. The debugger connected and attached but did not emit the expected initial break event, indicating a flaky or regressed behavior in the debugger's break-on-start signaling.", "confidence": 0.88, "relevant_files": ["test/parallel/test-debugger-exec.js", "test/common/debugger.js"], "relevant_tests": ["parallel/test-debugger-exec"], "evidence": [{"quote": "Error: Timeout (15000) while waiting for /break (?:on start )?in/i", "reason": "This is the explicit error thrown by the test framework when the debugger did not produce the expected initial break message within the 15-second timeout."}, {"quote": "at Object.waitForInitialBreak (/Users/runner/work/node/node/node/test/common/debugger.js:116:18)", "reason": "The stack trace shows the timeout originated in the waitForInitialBreak helper, confirming the debugger never sent the break-on-start signal."}, {"quote": "output: '< Debugger listening on ws://127.0.0.1:49508/1fd32687-38b3-450e-96e5-4a28a88f601e\\n' +\n    '< For help, see: https://nodejs.org/en/docs/inspector\\n' +\n    '< \\n' +\n    'connecting to 127.0.0.1:49508 ...\\n' +\n    ' ok\\n' +\n    '< Debugger attached.\\n'", "reason": "The debugger did connect and attach, but the output shows no break-on-start message was ever received, confirming the timeout was due to a missing event rather than a